ASIA 313L	Env Prob & Actvsm in China Lab	"Examines the rise of environmental social activism in China; the historical, political, cultural, and economic roots of China's current environmental problems, including deforestation, air pollution, water pollution, and species loss. Students learn theories of environmental justice and explore the rise of environmental activism in the PRC. The course will utilize pedagogical methods from InterGroup Dialogue (IGD) to provide students with the intellectual tools to analyze issues of power, privilege, and identity and by extension, their own position in the world in relation to these environmental issues."	HIST	1				
