COSC 480	Topics in Computer Science: Natural Language Processing	"Natural Language Processing systems (i.e., computational models capable of processing human languages) are ubiquitous in our daily lives. Internet search, translation systems, autocorrect, hate speech or fake news detectors all require computational systems that can comprehend human language. How can we build such systems and how can we evaluate whether the systems we build are truly comprehending human language? Students use a variety of techniques (such as n-gram models, Bayesian classifiers and neural networks) to build NLP systems. For each system built, students also confront its limitations by identifying and evaluating the system on critical edge cases."	COSC	3	COSC 202		Natural Sciences & Mathematics	
COSC 480L	Topics in Computer Science: User Interfaces Lab	Required corequisite to COSC 480.	COSC	1			Natural Sciences & Mathematics	
